[0m[33;1m[1;3mcommit dce954591363d9b40c8fdd488a5f641770c2d353
Author: Mathias Fussenegger <f.mathias@zignar.net>
Date:   Tue Oct 29 16:06:22 2024 +0100

    Remove mapping/setting distinction in TableParameters
    
    Currently a table's column policy is special in that opposed to all
    other table options set via `WITH (...)` it's not stored internally as a
    index setting but within the mapping.
    
    The `mapping` will be gone as part of https://github.com/crate/crate/issues/11939
    This is a first step into that direction.
    
    The storage format remains the same for now, but the client node no
    longer arranges `WITH` options into that format.

